    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1102">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> Files</note>
                <head>No. 1102<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">United States Delegation Working Paper</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1102fn1">This document is apparently an alternative to <ref
                            target="#d1103">document No. 1103</ref>. It bears the manuscript
                        notation “JD” [<persName corresp="#p_DJEJ1">Josiah
                        DuBois</persName>?].</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-25">July 25,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Position on Compensation for <gloss
                            target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Losses From Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Greece, Yugoslavia, and <persName corresp="#p_E1">Ethiopia</persName>,
                        shall file with the Allied Commission for Italy prior to November 1, 1945, a
                        statement of the nature and amount of the damage suffered by them as a
                        result of Italian military action.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Governments of the Soviet Union, the United Kingdom, and the United
                        States will consider such claims, in consultation with the other governments
                        concerned, for the purpose of determining the extent to which Italy shall be
                        required to make compensation by deliveries which will not in any way place
                        any burden for supporting the Italian peacetime economy on any other
                        country.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
